===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|busart|lang=fr}}, possibly from {{etyl|la}} {{term|buteon|buteōn|[[buteo]]|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈbʌzəɻd/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of several [[Old-World]] [[bird of prey|birds of prey]] with broad wings and a broad tail.
# In North America, a general term for scavenging birds such as the [[American black vulture]], also called [[American black buzzard]] (''[[Coragyps atratus]]''), and the [[turkey vulture]] (''[[Cathartes aura]]'').

